.V= $Header: getpid.2 1.6 86/05/13 $
.TH GETPID 2 "\*(V)" "4BSD"
.SH NAME
getpid, getppid \- get process identification
.SH SYNOPSIS
.ft 3
.nf
pid = getpid()
int pid;
.sp
ppid = getppid()
int ppid;
.fi
.ft 1
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Getpid
returns
the process ID of
the current process.
Most often it is used with the host identifier
.IR gethostid (2)
to generate uniquely-named temporary files.
.PP
.I Getppid
returns the process ID of the parent
of the current process. 
.SH "SEE ALSO
gethostid(2)
